  "prompt": "What can I do to be a good friend?",
  "response": "Here are some key ways to be a good friend:\n\n1. Be supportive and trustworthy\n- Listen actively when they need to talk\n- Offer help during difficult times\n- Keep their confidences\n\n2. Show genuine care and interest\n- Ask about their life and feelings\n- Remember important details\n- Check in regularly\n\n3. Be honest and reliable\n- Tell the truth, even when it's hard\n- Follow through on commitments\n- Be dependable\n\n4. Respect boundaries\n- Give them space when needed\n- Don't pressure them\n- Respect their opinions and choices\n\n5. Be positive and encouraging\n- Celebrate their successes\n- Offer constructive advice\n- Help boost their confidence\n\n6. Practice empathy\n- Try to understand their perspective\n- Show compassion\n- Validate their feelings\n\n7. Communicate openly\n- Address conflicts directly and kindly\n- Be willing to apologize\n- Give and receive feedback graciously\n\n8. Spend quality time together\n- Make time for shared activities\n- Be present and engaged\n- Create meaningful memories\n\n9. Accept them as they are\n- Don't try to change them\n- Appreciate their unique qualities\n- Support their personal growth\n\nRemember, good friendships are built on mutual respect, trust, and genuine care.",
